10. Continuation of Obligations
This Agreement will continue to bind the parties unless and until one or more of the following events occurs, at which point all obligations under this Agreement shall cease:

- Mutual agreement in writing by both Parties;
- Breach of any material provision of this Agreement by either Party, if such breach is not remedied within thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from the non-breaching Party;
- Insolvency or bankruptcy proceedings initiated by or against either Party;
- The complete performance by either Party of all their respective obligations under this Agreement;
- Termination by either Party for any reason, upon providing thirty (30) days' written notice to the other Party.
